children.subject: <md>A huge chunk of EECS 126 is CS 70 review -- I would say actually _most_ of the class is just CS 70 all over again (though others might disagree). If you were to take just CS 70 in the fall and really focus on doing well in it, EECS 126 will be relatively easy after that. I can't comment on Data 140 though.</md>
I can't seem to find Data 140 on CalCentral, is it confirmed for Fall 2022?

history.content:
Are taking both classes repetitive? I know EECS 126 covers more scho processes. 

I’m thinking CS 70 + Data 140 (Fall) -> EECS 126 (Spring). 

My reasoning is CS 70 and Data 140 will help prepare me for EECS 126. Is this a good move? I usually end up regretting classes that I take because I don’t feel prepared or didn’t take the right classes in the right order
